    "en": {
      "title": "Doing it with eggs\u2026",
      "author": "Sahan Weerasooriya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Take one teaspoon of egg white and add a big squeeze of lemon juice. Mix together, and apply it to your whole face, or just where you have large pores. Wait 15 minutes, then rinse with warm water, and pat dry.",
        "Apply a thin layer of pure egg whites to the skin (concentrate on areas where you see sagging \u2013 cheeks, jaw line, etc.). Be careful as you apply the mask. Allow to dry (usually 20 minutes), and then rinse off with cool water. (You can do this on your under eye bags, as well, but just be careful not to get it in your eye!)",
        "Take one egg yolk and mix together with one tablespoon coconut oil, or honey. Leave for 5-10 minutes and then rinse with warm water, and apply your favourite moisturizer.",
        "Mix 2-3 large egg whites and one tablespoon lemon juice. Apply the entire mixture to your scalp, before showering, and leave for 5-10 minutes, and then wash your hair with warm water. Applying egg whites to the scalp can also stimulate hair growth.",
        "Mix a whole egg, with an egg yolk, and a tablespoon of coconut oil (you can also use olive oil). Mix together and apply the whole mixture to the middle part of the hair, down through the ends (basically everywhere below the ears). Leave it for 5-10 minutes, and then wash your hair, as you normally would.",
        "Leave a Reply Cancel replyYour email address will not be published. Required fields are marked *Comment Name *",
        "Save my name, email, and website in this browser for the next time I comment."
      ],
